From: Trung Le <trung.le@ruby-journal.com>
Subject: dtsession: disable Motif color object inside dtsession itself

Modern Motif (2.3.x as shipped by Fedora) calls XConvertSelection on
_MOTIF_DEFAULT_COLORS from inside the Initialize method of widgets that
pull in the XmDisplay color object. For every CDE client that is fine:
the request is answered by the color server, which is dtsession.

Inside dtsession itself the request deadlocks: the call happens before
dtsession's main event loop starts, so dtsession cannot reply to its
own selection request. The visible symptom is dtsession hanging on the
loading screen right after login, never spawning dtwm. Confirmed via a
gdb stack trace showing dtsession blocked in _XmColorObjCreate ->
XtAppCreateShell -> Initialize -> XtAppProcessEvent -> poll().

Scoping the override to `Dtsession*useColorObj` keeps the color server
functional for every other Motif client. (An earlier draft set the
resource globally in Dt.ad, but that broke dtstyle's Color panel,
which explicitly checks useColorObj and refuses to operate when False.)

--- a/programs/dtsession/Dtsession.src
+++ b/programs/dtsession/Dtsession.src
@@ -33,3 +33,13 @@ Dtsession*ignoreEnvironment:	DISPLAY,SESSION_MANAGER,AUDIOSERVER
 !#  screen saver password, etc) for use in a Xinerama configuration.

 Dtsession*xineramaPreferredScreen:      0
+
+!# Disable Motif's per-process color object inside dtsession itself.
+!# Modern Motif (2.3.x as shipped by Fedora) issues XConvertSelection
+!# during widget Initialize to consult the color server -- but inside
+!# dtsession, the color server IS dtsession, and the request deadlocks
+!# (the main event loop has not started yet). The visible symptom is
+!# dtsession hanging on the loading screen after login, never spawning
+!# dtwm. Scoping to Dtsession only keeps the color server functional
+!# for every other CDE client.
+Dtsession*useColorObj:	False
